27/01/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- It became official on Monday (January 26th): former Interior Minister Ljubomir Frckovski is the opposition Macedonian Social Democratic Union's (SDSM) candidate for president in the March 22nd elections. 
All 700 delegates present at the party's convention voted in favour of Frckovski's nomination. 
Late on Sunday, Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski's ruling party, VMRO-DPMNE, tapped university professor Georgi Ivanov as its candidate. 
(Makfax, MIA - 26/01/09)
